      <hedline>
        <hl1>Le Provocateur</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mark Zucker letter takes issue with Emily Eakin's September 10 article on French novelist Michel Houellebecq (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Michel Houellebecq's blend of anomie, Stalinism, sexual hedonism, sensory-deprivation and reported homophobia is full of contradictions (Emily Eakin, Sept. 10). His approval of Stalin's murder of anarchists is a case in point. Perhaps ''le provocateur'' should contemplate the meaning of a bullet in the back of the head. Joseph Stalin would have had no problem liquidating Houellebecq's acute case of anomie.</p>
        <p>Mark Zucker  Southfield, Mich.</p>
      </block>
